{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:26:49.314Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"fqbq2ydl","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/README.md:1-EOF","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Local MVP Backend Foundation\n  2 | \n  3 | Welcome to the local FastAPI MVP backend foundation for the GFF AI Enterprise platform. This module provides local developer API capabilities, SQLite storage connectivity, system health monitoring, and a fully configured local CORS workspace to interface seamlessly with the Next.js frontend.\n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## 🚀 Quick Start (Root Convenience Commands)\n  8 | \n  9 | For rapid development, convenience scripts have been added to the repository's root `package.json`. These allow you to manage and run the backend seamlessly without manually creating or activating Python virtual environments in your active terminal.\n 10 | \n 11 | From the **root directory** of the project, you can run:\n 12 | \n 13 | *   **Install Backend Dependencies & Environment Setup**:\n 14 |     ```bash\n 15 |     npm run backend:install\n 16 |     ```\n 17 |     *This automatically creates the Python virtual environment (`venv`), installs all required pip dependencies, and copies `.env.example` to `.env` if not already present.*\n 18 | \n 19 | *   **Initialize & Seed Local SQLite Database**:\n 20 |     ```bash\n 21 |     npm run backend:seed\n 22 |     ```\n 23 |     *This executes the database seeder to bootstrap SQLite (`dev.db`) with multi-tenant enterprise development data (including GFF Admin, Apex Tenant Admin, Apex Client Members, as well as mock client accounts, projects, support tickets, invoices, and compliance logs).*\n 24 | \n 25 | *   **Run Backend Development Server (FastAPI)**:\n 26 |     ```bash\n 27 |     npm run backend:dev\n 28 |     ```\n 29 |     *Starts the FastAPI application via Uvicorn on [http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000) with hot-reloading enabled.*\n 30 | \n 31 | *   **Run Backend Security, RBAC & End-To-End Smoke Tests**:\n 32 |     ```bash\n 33 |     npm run backend:check\n 34 |     ```\n 35 |     *Executes both the security utility suite (`test_security_utilities.py`) and the comprehensive pytest-driven smoke tests (`test_backend_smoke.py`). It validates: JWT parsing, bcrypt hashing, RBAC rules, health endpoints, user profile retrieval (`/auth/me`), multi-tenant data boundaries, client dashboard scoping, projects listing, and support ticket creation isolation.*\n 36 | \n 37 | ---\n 38 | \n 39 | ## Architecture Overview\n 40 | \n 41 | The backend uses a standard, modular clean-architecture layout built for Python 3.12+ and FastAPI:\n 42 | \n 43 | ```text\n 44 | backend/\n 45 | ├── app/\n 46 | │   ├── __init__.py\n 47 | │   ├── api.py           # Core endpoints (Health, SystemLogs)\n 48 | │   ├── config.py        # Settings & Pydantic Config Validation\n 49 | │   ├── database.py      # SQLAlchemy DB Connection & Dependency Injection\n 50 | │   ├── main.py          # FastAPI App Entrypoint & CORS Middleware\n 51 | │   ├── models.py        # SQLAlchemy Declarative Models\n 52 | │   └── schemas.py       # Pydantic Schemas (V2)\n 53 | ├── .env.example         # Template for environment configuration\n 54 | ├── .gitignore           # Local development ignores\n 55 | ├── README.md            # Execution manual\n 56 | └── requirements.txt     # Python Dependencies\n 57 | ```\n 58 | \n 59 | ## Features\n 60 | \n 61 | - **Automated DB Bootstrap**: Automatically boots a local SQLite database (`dev.db`) on application launch.\n 62 | - **Enterprise Logs**: A simple, high-performance database logger schema for auditing backend/frontend handshakes.\n 63 | - **Health Verification**: An endpoint at `/api/v1/health` that dynamically validates database status and platform health.\n 64 | - **Next.js Alignment**: Built-in CORS and request timing telemetry middleware matching frontend-dev requirements.\n 65 | - **Clean Interactive Specs**: Automatic redirect of root `/` path to the interactive OpenAPI UI (`/docs`).\n 66 | \n 67 | ---\n 68 | \n 69 | ## Local Setup & Run Guide\n 70 | \n 71 | ### 1. Prerequisites\n 72 | Ensure you have **Python 3.12+** and **pip** installed:\n 73 | ```bash\n 74 | python3 --version\n 75 | pip3 --version\n 76 | ```\n 77 | \n 78 | ### 2. Set Up Virtual Environment\n 79 | Move to the backend folder and create a clean Python virtual environment:\n 80 | ```bash\n 81 | cd backend\n 82 | python3 -m venv venv\n 83 | ```\n 84 | \n 85 | Activate the environment:\n 86 | - **macOS / Linux**:\n 87 |   ```bash\n 88 |   source venv/bin/activate\n 89 |   ```\n 90 | - **Windows**:\n 91 |   ```bash\n 92 |   venv\\Scripts\\activate\n 93 |   ```\n 94 | \n 95 | ### 3. Install Dependencies\n 96 | ```bash\n 97 | pip install -r requirements.txt\n 98 | ```\n 99 | \n100 | ### 4. Set Up Environment Config\n101 | Copy the example environment file:\n102 | ```bash\n103 | cp .env.example .env\n104 | ```\n105 | The defaults in `.env` are pre-tuned for seamless local development with the Next.js local frontend.\n106 | \n107 | > ⚠️ **Production Security Warning**:\n108 | > In local development mode, `JWT_SECRET` defaults to a safe developer-only fallback key. However, for any production deployment, you **MUST** override `JWT_SECRET` in your environment variables with a cryptographically secure, high-entropy key (e.g., generated via `openssl rand -hex 32`). Leaving the default key active in production compromises token verification and authentication security.\n109 | \n110 | ### 5. Seed the Local Database\n111 | Seed the SQLite database with representative GFF AI multi-tenant development data (including 4 client accounts, 4 projects, 4 agent operations, 4 documents, 4 invoices, 3 support tickets, and 3 governance compliance records) and pre-configured role-based development users:\n112 | \n113 | ```bash\n114 | python app/seed.py\n115 | ```\n116 | \n117 | #### Pre-Configured Developer Accounts & Roles:\n118 | - **GFF Admin Lead** (Global Operations):\n119 |   - Email: `gff_admin@gff.ai`\n120 |   - Role: `gff_admin`\n121 |   - Password: `password123`\n122 | - **Apex Admin Lead** (Client Tenant Admin):\n123 |   - Email: `client_admin@apex.com`\n124 |   - Role: `client_admin`\n125 |   - Tenant: Apex Global\n126 |   - Password: `password123`\n127 | - **Apex Analyst** (Client Tenant Member):\n128 |   - Email: `client_member@apex.com`\n129 |   - Role: `client_member`\n130 |   - Tenant: Apex Global\n131 |   - Password: `password123`\n132 | - **Legacy Fallback Admin**:\n133 |   - Email: `admin@gff.ai`\n134 |   - Role: `admin`\n135 |   - Password: `gff_enterprise_admin_pass_2026`\n136 | - **Legacy Fallback Client**:\n137 |   - Email: `client@chevron.com`\n138 |   - Role: `client`\n139 |   - Tenant: Chevron Corporation\n140 |   - Password: `chevron_secure_pass_2026`\n141 | \n142 | #### Idempotency & Database Resetting:\n143 | - Running `python app/seed.py` repeatedly is perfectly **idempotent**; it checks for existing records before inserting, ensuring no duplicated keys or rows.\n144 | - To safely **wipe all tables and fresh-seed** a clean slate, run with the `--reset` flag:\n145 |   ```bash\n146 |   python app/seed.py --reset\n147 |   ```\n148 | \n149 | ### 6. Run the Server\n150 | Launch the development server via Uvicorn:\n151 | ```bash\n152 | uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000\n153 | ```\n154 | \n155 | Once running, you can access:\n156 | - **Interactive OpenAPI Documentation**: [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)\n157 | - **Service Health Check Endpoint**: [http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health](http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health)\n158 | \n159 | ---\n160 | \n161 | ## API Documentation\n162 | \n163 | ### GET `/api/v1/health`\n164 | Checks backend and database health.\n165 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n166 | ```json\n167 | {\n168 |   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n169 |   \"timestamp\": 1719493200.0,\n170 |   \"database\": {\n171 |     \"status\": \"healthy\",\n172 |     \"error\": null\n173 |   },\n174 |   \"services\": {\n175 |     \"api\": \"healthy\",\n176 |     \"gff_core\": \"operational\"\n177 |   },\n178 |   \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n179 | }\n180 | ```\n181 | \n182 | ### GET `/api/v1/logs`\n183 | Returns the recent list of system log entries.\n184 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n185 | ```json\n186 | []\n187 | ```\n188 | \n189 | ### POST `/api/v1/logs`\n190 | Creates a test system log.\n191 | **Request Payload**:\n192 | ```json\n193 | {\n194 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n195 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n196 |   \"module\": \"handshake\"\n197 | }\n198 | ```\n199 | **Response (201 Created)**:\n200 | ```json\n201 | {\n202 |   \"id\": 1,\n203 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n204 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n205 |   \"module\": \"handshake\",\n206 |   \"created_at\": \"2026-06-27T15:10:00.000000\"\n207 | }\n208 | ```","success":true}],"durationMs":6}}
